cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.NI 

This paper discusses security threats in cloud computing, specifically related to memory DoS attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper also discusses the impact of these attacks on distributed applications and the need for a defense system based on performance counter measurements.
